<br>
Well a few things you should probably know then.<br>
<br>
First of all, and most importantly, let me start with this. If you are here cause we are l33t, we rule, we roXorz, das uber, and think that because of these things you can complete your epic, get phat lewtz, or simply become level 60 you are in the wrong place. Even if you say you arent, our members have a way of seeing through people. So if that is really why you are here, please be honest with us and yourself, and don’t waste either or our time.<br>
<br>
Secondly, we don’t recruit. There is no formal process of voting, pledging, petitioning, applications, jumping through hoops, level requirements, etc. We are a family of players, the only way to get in is to be adopted into the family. So how exactly do you get into Ashborne then? You just need to make yourself so loved by us that we cant figure out why you arent in the guild. (that’s when you get guilded) <br>
<br>
Now, just to help you out, let me give you a couple of pointers on how to become loved by Ashborne:<br>
<br>
1. You have to seek us out. We are not gonna come looking for you just because you posted something nice on our public forum. You wanna get to know us, you better introduce yourself.<br>
2. While getting to know us, do not spam, beg, or generally annoy guildmembers while looking for groups. Also, we don’t take guests on big raids, so you have to get to know us in small group settings, getting XP and such.<br>
3. Yes, we have people that handle new membership applications. No, you don’t get to know who they are (I am not one of them). You goal, is to get yourself noticed by enough of the guild that one of them contacts you.<br>
4. Be patient. Most new people take 2-3 months before they get guilded. Yeah, that’s what it takes.<br>
<br>
A few things not to do:<br>
<br>
1. Do not send tells saying, “I wanna join Ashborne, can I group with you?”<br>
2. Do not ask us, “How much longer till I get guilded?”<br>
3. Do not send us tells if you are under level 50. Everyone in our guild is currently 52+ and there really wont be anyone for you to group with until you are at least 50. Go level up so you can group with us.<br>
4. Do not feed Tinomen cookies. There was a rumor going around that your could bribe your way into Ashborne with sweets. This is not true, and anyone found feeding the Ogre will be shot on sight<br>
<br>
This process may sound strict, or hard, or confusing, but this is how we have always done things. If you want some idea of how often we guild people, read the rest of this public forum. Pretty much most of the people posting their interest in Ashborne never make it past the first week. However, I can tell you that we are a close group of people in a guild that truly loves and enjoys each other, and no one has regretted the wait. If you are still interested, then I suggest you read the do’s and don’ts listed above one more time, and then get started.<br>
<br>
Best of luck, I hope to see you in the family, <p>Siayrx <br>
